By Kingsley Chukwuka
The Plateau State chapter of the Nigerian Hunters and Forest Security Services (NHFSS), has appointed the Plateau State Gubernatorial Candidate of the Labour Party Amb. Yohanna Margif as its Grand Patron.
State Commander of the Nigerian Hunters and Forest Security Services, Amb. Dabat Nienmoup while presenting the certificate of confirmation to Margif as a Ground Patron of NHFSS at a brief Ceremony held in Jos on Sunday the honor is to appreciate his contributions and support to security development of the State as well as his Philanthropist works.
He assured the Labour Party Governorship Candidate of their unflinching Support always.
Responding, Margif promised to prioritize Security of lives and properties if elected Governor of the State.
He explained that the State has had it’s own share of Insecurity Which has resulted in the loss of lives and properties, saying he has already developed security blueprint and strategies to collaborate with experts to ensure that Plateau is secured.
 
